886
1:1:49,8 --> 1:1:52,563
You heard Hitch and me
yelling at each other, is that it?


887
1:1:52,563 --> 1:1:56,362
Come on now, cookie.
Don't go taking it that serious.


888
1:1:56,362 --> 1:2:0,697
You know how Hitch and me are,
always rowing about something.


889
1:2:0,697 --> 1:2:2,787
He don't mean what he says half the time.


890
1:2:2,787 --> 1:2:6,26
By tomorrow we'll both of us forget
all about it...


891
1:2:6,26 --> 1:2:7,872
Everything's okay.


892
1:2:7,872 --> 1:2:9,742
Don't let a thing like that get you down.


893
1:2:9,742 --> 1:2:14,476
You run along now see your sailor boy.
Stop being that way.


894
1:2:14,476 --> 1:2:18,88
No, mommy. I'm going to tell Tony
I can't marry him.


895
1:2:18,88 --> 1:2:21,415
But you must marry him, snooks.


896
1:2:21,415 --> 1:2:23,247
After all we talked over?


897
1:2:23,247 --> 1:2:27,783
I'm counting on it.
You don't know how much it means to me.


898
1:2:27,783 --> 1:2:30,376
No, mommy.
I just can't, that's all.


899
1:2:30,376 --> 1:2:31,911
Now you listen to me, young lady.


900
1:2:31,911 --> 1:2:35,168
I'm your ma, and I say you're going right down
to dinner and fix it up.


901
1:2:35,168 --> 1:2:36,904
and there'll be no more talk about it.


902
1:2:36,904 --> 1:2:40,192
All right, mommy.
I'll fix it up.


903
1:2:40,192 --> 1:2:45,124
And when I come to the theater tonight
I wanna be sure you're gonna tell me everything's okay.


904
1:2:45,124 --> 1:2:47,436
It will be.
It will be.


905
1:2:47,436 --> 1:2:50,299
Come on now, kitten.


906
1:2:50,299 --> 1:2:53,83
You gotta do this.
And don't worry about me.


907
1:2:53,83 --> 1:2:56,509
I'm not a black number yet.


908
1:2:56,509 --> 1:5:53,207
I know, mommy.


909
1:5:53,207 --> 1:5:55,224
Boy, that's happy music.


910
1:5:55,224 --> 1:5:57,355
Just for us.


911
1:5:57,355 --> 1:6:0,54
Wanna dance?
No.


912
1:6:0,54 --> 1:6:2,845
Wish you didn't have to work tonight.
We could go to Coney Island.


913
1:6:2,845 --> 1:6:4,285
I don't like Coney Island.


914
1:6:4,285 --> 1:6:6,708
Aw, come on, you don't.
You did the other night.


915
1:6:6,708 --> 1:6:8,461
That was the other night.


916
1:6:8,461 --> 1:6:10,308
What's the matter with you, honey?


917
1:6:10,308 --> 1:6:12,103
Why? Nothing.


918
1:6:12,103 --> 1:6:13,532
Oh, yes there is.


919
1:6:13,532 --> 1:6:16,985
Come on, let's have it.


920
1:6:16,985 --> 1:6:19,237
Tony, I'll tell you.


921
1:6:19,237 --> 1:6:22,96
I don't know how to say it, but...


922
1:6:22,96 --> 1:6:25,44
Tony, I don't want to get married.


923
1:6:25,44 --> 1:6:27,814
Say, don't say things like that,
I got a week heart.


924
1:6:27,814 --> 1:6:30,371
Tony, I mean it.


925
1:6:30,371 --> 1:6:33,334
I like you an awful lot
and all that...


926
1:6:33,334 --> 1:6:36,724
but I just can't think of getting married
right now.


927
1:6:36,724 --> 1:6:40,3
What's the matter, honey?
What's happened?


928
1:6:40,3 --> 1:6:41,566
Nothing.


929
1:6:41,566 --> 1:6:45,911
I don't think you'll be able to understand, but...


930
1:6:45,911 --> 1:6:47,854
Being born on the stage and all


931
1:6:47,854 --> 1:6:51,892
well, getting married and leaving,
it seems to be giving up everything.


932
1:6:51,892 --> 1:6:55,4
You told me the other night
you wanted to get out of the show business.


933
1:6:55,4 --> 1:6:56,774
That's how I thought I felt.


934
1:6:56,774 --> 1:7:1,935
When I come right down to it,
I just can't, that's all.


935
1:7:1,935 --> 1:7:3,593
You'll never know, Tony,


936
1:7:3,593 --> 1:7:6,417
what it feels like to be on the other side
of those footlights.


937
1:7:6,417 --> 1:7:8,904
and to hear them clap and clap for you.


938
1:7:8,904 --> 1:7:11,803
It does something to a girl.


939
1:7:11,803 --> 1:7:14,62
I don't know what.


940
1:7:14,62 --> 1:7:16,789
April, I don't believe a word you're saying.


941
1:7:16,789 --> 1:7:20,26
Either you're lying to me
or else you've just been kidding yourself.


942
1:7:20,26 --> 1:7:22,617
Now, come on,
let's dance and forget about it.


943
1:7:22,617 --> 1:7:25,607
I don't want to dance.


944
1:7:25,607 --> 1:7:29,508
I want you to get it through your head
right now.


945
1:7:29,508 --> 1:7:31,542
This is it, really.


946
1:7:31,542 --> 1:7:34,836
Mother signed a new contract today
for a new show.


947
1:7:34,836 --> 1:7:39,386
And there's a chance
for me to go with her in a splendid part.


948
1:7:39,386 --> 1:7:43,161
If I don't take it
I know I'll be sorry all my life.


949
1:7:43,161 --> 1:7:45,693
Then we'll both be miserable.


950
1:7:45,693 --> 1:7:48,31
But listen, honey.
That's no life for you.


951
1:7:48,31 --> 1:7:53,873
Well, I'm not so sure that married life
in some godforsaken farm is a life for me either.


952
1:7:53,873 --> 1:7:56,7
After all, I'm young.
People tell me I'm pretty.


953
1:7:56,7 --> 1:7:58,379
Here I've got a big chance.


954
1:7:58,379 --> 1:8:0,616
I might be a star.


955
1:8:0,616 --> 1:8:3,703
Now, I ask you, Tony...


956
1:8:3,703 --> 1:8:7,923
what girl wouldn't grab at the chance
to land on Broadway in a big show?


957
1:8:7,923 --> 1:8:10,73
None, I suppose.


958
1:8:10,73 --> 1:8:11,873
Not since you're locked to them.


959
1:8:11,873 --> 1:8:17,567
Let's pray it ended up
with nothing to be locked with right now.


960
1:8:17,567 --> 1:8:22,323
Tony, don't look at me like that.


961
1:8:22,323 --> 1:8:24,127
Makes me feel terrible.


962
1:8:24,127 --> 1:8:27,783
I really think
you're an awfully sweet boy, but


963
1:8:27,783 --> 1:8:32,777
after all, when it comes to love,
why, I've only known you five days.


964
1:8:32,777 --> 1:8:36,376
You think of jumping into something


965
1:8:36,376 --> 1:8:39,434
and giving up a whole career...


966
1:8:39,434 --> 1:8:42,17
Well, Tony, you ought to understand.


967
1:8:42,17 --> 1:8:42,857
Sure.


968
1:8:42,857 --> 1:8:45,633
I mean,
we'll still have lots of fun together.


969
1:8:45,633 --> 1:8:50,239
Just the same. Go to lots of parties.
Why, we might even still be engaged.


970
1:8:50,239 --> 1:8:53,554
No. I wouldn't want to feel
like I'm tying you down.


971
1:8:53,554 --> 1:8:56,773
Guess I'd better go back to my ship.


972
1:8:56,773 --> 1:9:1,587
You mean, enlist again?
Yeah.


973
1:9:1,587 --> 1:9:4,219
Sailing for the West Indies.


974
1:9:4,219 --> 1:9:6,45
I've always wanted to see the West Indies.


975
1:9:6,45 --> 1:9:7,882
But you'll come back.


976
1:9:7,882 --> 1:9:12,533
Sure, some day.


977
1:9:12,533 --> 1:9:15,836
What time is it?


978
1:9:15,836 --> 1:9:17,916
Eight o'clock, almost.


979
1:9:17,916 --> 1:9:19,59
I could just make it if I hurry.


980
1:9:19,59 --> 1:9:22,88
Tony!


981
1:9:22,88 --> 1:9:24,536
You're angry with me.


982
1:9:24,536 --> 1:9:27,52
I didn't want you to be.


983
1:9:27,52 --> 1:9:32,129
Tony, please try not to hate me.


984
1:9:32,129 --> 1:9:34,188
Please try to understand.


985
1:9:34,188 --> 1:9:37,584
This was the best way for us both.


986
1:9:37,584 --> 1:9:40,893
I don't hate you.
I just gotta hurry, that's all.


987
1:9:40,893 --> 1:9:44,576
You ought to be getting down
to your show too, don't you?


988
1:9:44,576 --> 1:9:47,245
I'll walk to the subway with you.
It's on my way.


989
1:9:47,245 --> 1:9:49,352
You'll be late.
I don't care.


990
1:9:49,352 --> 1:10:26,16
Check, please.


991
1:10:26,16 --> 1:10:30,308
Seventh floor, mam.
Good night, Jim, I'll see you in the morning.


992
1:10:30,308 --> 1:10:58,659
Good night, honey.


993
1:10:58,659 --> 1:10:59,766
Well,


994
1:10:59,766 --> 1:11:1,891
thanks for coming down with me, April.


995
1:11:1,891 --> 1:11:52,509
Oh, that was all right.


996
1:11:52,509 --> 1:11:55,839
Well, here's my train.


997
1:11:55,839 --> 1:11:57,576
Bye, April.


998
1:11:57,576 --> 1:12:53,729
Bye, Tony.


999
1:12:53,729 --> 1:12:57,253
Don't cry, kid.
There'll be another one along any minute.


1000
1:12:57,253 --> 1:13:49,796
Cheer up.


1001
1:13:49,796 --> 1:13:52,608
April!


1002
1:13:52,608 --> 1:13:57,419
April!


1003
1:13:57,419 --> 1:14:9,511
April!


1004
1:14:9,511 --> 1:14:14,816
April! April!


1005
1:14:14,816 --> 1:14:21,434
Aw, be quiet!


1006
1:14:21,434 --> 1:14:23,4
Where's April?
Where's April?


1007
1:14:23,4 --> 1:14:27,962
Mother!
What's the matter?


1008
1:14:27,962 --> 1:14:30,688
Help me to my dressing room


1009
1:14:30,688 --> 1:14:32,368
Well I'll be...


1010
1:14:32,368 --> 1:14:34,368
Where did she get?


1011
1:14:34,368 --> 1:14:39,24
Mother, you're sick.
Don't worry about me.


1012
1:14:39,24 --> 1:14:41,746
Is everything all right?
Everything's fine.


1013
1:14:41,746 --> 1:14:43,81
Are you gonna be married right away?


1014
1:14:43,81 --> 1:14:46,5
No, I sent him back to his ship, ma.


1015
1:14:46,5 --> 1:14:49,747
What's this you're saying?
You lie down, you'll feel better.


1016
1:14:49,747 --> 1:14:52,505
Tell me, tell me.
Don't worry, it's all over.


1017
1:14:52,505 --> 1:14:53,818
I sent him away.


1018
1:14:53,818 --> 1:14:56,355
I guess it is jolly life on board.


1019
1:14:56,355 --> 1:14:58,514
It's a good thing we found out in time.


1020
1:14:58,514 --> 1:15:1,106
Oh, nothing matters now but you, mommy.


1021
1:15:1,106 --> 1:15:3,508
We'll always have each other.


1022
1:15:3,508 --> 1:15:6,247
Nothing's ever going to separate us again.


1023
1:15:6,247 --> 1:15:9,707
Oh, my God. What have you done?
What have I done?


1024
1:15:9,707 --> 1:15:11,466
Mommy, you're not well.


1025
1:15:11,466 --> 1:15:15,516
My baby, my little baby.


1026
1:15:15,516 --> 1:15:18,608
Well, this is a swell time to be showing up
for a Saturday night show.


1027
1:15:18,608 --> 1:15:20,388
What's the matter with her?
Drunk?


1028
1:15:20,388 --> 1:15:22,98
Well, what if she is?


1029
1:15:22,98 --> 1:15:26,101
Drunk as a fool,
look at her lying there, the gin-soaked old...


1030
1:15:26,101 --> 1:15:29,78
You let my mother alone!
You men make me sick.


1031
1:15:29,78 --> 1:15:30,537
You don't care about anything


1032
1:15:30,537 --> 1:15:33,24
as long as you can shove somebody
on your filthy stage.


1033
1:15:33,24 --> 1:15:35,136
and make them shake for a bunch of gorillas.


1034
1:15:35,136 --> 1:15:37,336
Yeah? Well that talk don't get me anywhere.


1035
1:15:37,336 --> 1:15:40,168
So far as I'm concerned Kitty Darling's finished.


1036
1:15:40,168 --> 1:15:43,812
Here I talk to Gus Weinbaum
trying to keep her in the show here...


1037
1:15:43,812 --> 1:15:48,382
and look at her, blind, paralyzed,
Saturday night with nobody to take her place.


1038
1:15:48,382 --> 1:15:50,288
I'll take her place.


1039
1:15:50,288 --> 1:15:52,961
I'll get out there and get those gorillas
your money's worth.


1040
1:15:52,961 --> 1:15:54,19
Now what do you think of that?


1041
1:15:54,19 --> 1:15:57,937
Me take a chance on a dumb chorus girl
to fill a specialty number?


1042
1:15:57,937 --> 1:15:59,56
You're crazy!


1043
1:15:59,56 --> 1:16:1,152
Listen, she ain't so dumb.
I've been rehearsing her for weeks.


1044
1:16:1,152 --> 1:16:2,351
She's swell, I'm telling ya.


1045
1:16:2,351 --> 1:16:5,336
Anyway ain't it be better
take a chance with the kid?


1046
1:16:5,336 --> 1:16:8,462
Well, maybe it is.
Hop to it, kid. But you'd better be good.


1047
1:16:8,462 --> 1:16:11,51
Come on, baby, wake up.
Oh, I'll be good all right.


1048
1:16:11,51 --> 1:16:13,163
I'll get out and give them what they want.


1049
1:16:13,163 --> 1:16:16,12
I'll show them, I'll show them!
Now you're talkin'.


1050
1:16:16,12 --> 1:16:19,495
You get out of my way.


1051
1:16:19,495 --> 1:17:44,872
Well I'll be...


1052
1:17:44,872 --> 1:17:46,843
Come on, get out there and play again.
No!


1053
1:17:46,843 --> 1:17:50,569
Come on, get out there.
No!


1054
1:17:50,569 --> 1:17:53,457
Come on, girls, get out there.
Do something.


1055
1:17:53,457 --> 1:17:55,728
Go ahead, get onstage there...


1056
1:17:55,728 --> 1:17:59,64
Come on, you get onstage too.


1057
1:17:59,64 --> 1:18:2,969
Tony!
Tony!


1058
1:18:2,969 --> 1:18:5,115
I came back because I thought,
well, maybe...


1059
1:18:5,115 --> 1:18:9,165
Take me away from this terrible place.


1060
1:18:9,165 --> 1:18:10,397
You mean it?


1061
1:18:10,397 --> 1:18:12,835
I never want to be in the stage again.


1062
1:18:12,835 --> 1:18:14,939
You know, I had a hunch
you weren't telling me the truth.


1063
1:18:14,939 --> 1:18:16,898
Aw, come on, what's it all about?


1064
1:18:16,898 --> 1:18:18,641
It's mother.


1065
1:18:18,641 --> 1:18:21,362
Tony, I can't go away and leave her now.


1066
1:18:21,362 --> 1:18:24,408
She's sick. She needs a home.


1067
1:18:24,408 --> 1:18:26,359
Then let her come with us.
That'll be swell.


1068
1:18:26,359 --> 1:18:29,663
Come on, let's go in and talk to her.
I bet I can make her see it our way.


1069
1:18:29,663 --> 1:18:31,929
It would be wonderful if she would.


1070
1:18:31,929 --> 1:18:35,419
We'll always be together, won't we?


1071
1:18:35,419 --> 1:18:38,902
Yes, honey.
All three of us.


1072
1:18:38,902 --> 1:18:43,991
All three of us.


1073
1:18:43,991 --> 1:20:43,991
Subtitles: Lus Filipe Bernardes


